Package: disperseR
Type: Package
Title: Run HYSPLIT Many Times in Parallel, Aggregate to ZIP Code Level
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lucas", "Henneman", email = "lhenneman@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Christine", "Choirat", role = "aut"),
    person("Maja", "Garbulinska", role = "aut")
    )
Author: Lucas Henneman [aut, cre],
    Christine Choirat [aut],
    Maja Garbulinska [aut]
Maintainer: Lucas Henneman <lhenneman@gmail.com>
Description: Runs HYSPLIT many times and calculates the HYSPLIT Average
    Dispersion (HyADS) exposure metric. Results can be aggregated to ZIP code
    level to create national estimates of exposure from various sources. Uses
    modern spatial libraries (sf, terra). HYSPLIT binaries can be provided via
    the optional 'splitr' package (available from GitHub at
    <https://github.com/rich-iannone/splitr>) or via explicit binary paths.
URL: https://github.com/josbyb2020/disperseR-test2026
BugReports: https://github.com/josbyb2020/disperseR-test2026/issues
License: GPL-3
